<HEADLINE>
<P>
WILLIAM HALL WENDEL RETIRED INDUSTRIALIST AND EXECUTIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
William Hall Wendel, 76, retired president of the Carborundum Co. and the 
Kennecott Copper Corp. Graduated from the U.S. Naval Academy and the Harvard 
Business School, Wendel joined Carborundum after World War II, rising to 
president by 1962. 
</P>
<P>
When Carborundum was sold to Kennecott in 1977, he became president of 
Kennecott, retiring in 1980. During his retirement, he served five years as 
chairman of Polaris Industries, Minneapolis manufacturer of all-terrain 
vehicles. On Dec. 3 in Savannah, Ga., of a heart attack. 
</P>
</TEXT>
