<P>
FRANCISCO GABILONDO SOLER; SONGWRITER KNOWN AS 'CRI-CRI' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Francisco Gabilondo Soler, 83, the children's songwriter known as "Cri-Cri" 
whose compositions have been sung throughout the Spanish-speaking world. 
Gabilondo Soler wrote and performed hundreds of songs that captivated Mexican 
radio audiences for years and made his nickname -- from a child's word for 
cricket -- a household word throughout his country. In Mexico City on Friday of 
a heart attack. 
</P>
