<P>
PREP BASKETBALL TOURNAMENTS; 
</P>
<P>
MARINA TOP-SEEDED AT IRVINE; CERRITOS, WESTERN CO-FAVORITES AT FULLERTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Marina High School, led by All-American center Cherokee Parks, is the 
top-seeded team in the Irvine World News basketball tournament that begins 
Tuesday ) at three high schools. 
</P>
<P>
Marina (3-3) has struggled in the opening three weeks of the season but was 
runner-up to Tustin in the Trabuco Hills tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Capistrano Valley (5-1) is seeded second in the tournament and Irvine (6-0) 
third. Capistrano Valley features center Brett McCorkle and guard Tom Airey. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine is led by forward John Molle, who is averaging 33.2 points. Irvine won 
the Daily Pilot Tipoff Classic at Newport Harbor two weeks ago. 
</P>
<P>
Loara guard Tes Whitlock, the county's leading scorer, will also compete in the 
Irvine tournament. Whitlock scored 117 points in three games last week in the 
Tournament of Champions at Ocean View. 
</P>
<P>
Other top players competing include center Darren Galloway (Kennedy), guard Joe 
Foss (Esperanza), forward Chauncy Woolridge (Santa Ana), forward Doug Hesse 
(Corona del Mar) and forward Brandon Jessie (Edison). 
</P>
<P>
The championship game is scheduled for 7 p.m. Saturday at Christ College 
Irvine. Tuesday's first-round pairings: 
</P>
<P>
At Irvine: 4:30 p.m. -- Kennedy vs. Mission Viejo; 6 -- Marina vs. Saddleback; 
7:30 -- Brea-Olinda vs. Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
At University: 6 p.m. -- Santa Ana vs. Corona del Mar; 7:30 -- Esperanza vs. 
University. 
</P>
<P>
At Woodbridge: 4:30 -- Edison vs. Loara; 6 -- Capistrano Valley vs. Savanna; 
7:30 -- Orange Lutheran vs. Woodbridge. 
</P>
<P>
Cerritos and Western high schools are co-favorites in the seventh Fullerton 
Classic that begins Tuesday at Fullerton High School. 
</P>
<P>
Cerritos, the defending tournament champion, features 6-foot-8 center Mark 
Flick. Western (5-0) is one of two undefeated teams in the county. 
</P>
<P>
Western has a balanced attack in guard Tom Barraza (15.8 points), guard Chris 
Jackson (15.8) and forward Steve Siefken (14.2). Jackson is shooting 62% from 
the field. 
</P>
<P>
Other top players competing in the eight-team tournament include guard Mark 
Perry (Garden Grove), forward Angel Barrios (Buena Park) and guard Chris 
