<P>
PORTLAND TURNS BACK ORLANDO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PORTLAND, Ore. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Clyde Drexler scored 31 points, and Buck Williams had 26 points and 20 rebounds 
as the Portland Trail Blazers overcame a fourth-quarter rally by Orlando to 
beat the Magic, 126-107, Sunday night. 
</P>
<P>
Scott Skiles, who scored 21 points for Orlando, converted a three-point play 
with 8:16 left, capping a 16-0 run that gave the Magic a 99-95 lead. 
</P>
<P>
The Trail Blazers, who led, 95-83, at the end of the third quarter, missed 
their first 10 shots of the fourth quarter, but followed Orlando's 16-0 run 
with a 15-0 spurt of their own. 
</P>
<P>
Drexler's three-point shot with 5:54 left put Portland ahead to stay, 100-99. 
Terry Porter's two free throws with 3:42 remaining made it 110-99, completing 
the 15-0 run. 
</P>
<P>
The Magic closed to 111-105 on a layup by Nick Anderson with 2:18 left, but 
Portland finished the game with a 15-2 run. 
</P>
