<TEXT>
<P>
A prisoner who escaped from the downtown County Jail on Friday -- just hours 
after he had been sentenced to 10 years in prison for assault with a deadly 
weapon -- was captured early Sunday in North Park, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Robert Anthony O'Donnell was captured about 4 a.m. in the 3300 block of Herman 
Avenue after officers received a report of a prowler at a house in the nearby 
3300 block of 31st Street. 
</P>
<P>
O'Donnell was captured after he was spotted running from the house, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
O'Donnell was taken back to jail and held on suspicion of escape and attempted 
burglary, police said. 
</P>
<P>
