<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: THOUSAND OAKS; 
</P>
<P>
MAN TO BE ARRAIGNED ON STEROIDS CHARGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PSYCHE PASCUAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Thousand Oaks salesman of mail-order vitamins was released from Ventura 
County Jail on Sunday after he was arrested on suspicion of possession of 
illegal steroids for sale. 
</P>
<P>
Lawrence Woods, 43, was released on his own recognizance, a jail official said. 
</P>
<P>
He is scheduled for arraignment at 8:30 a.m. Friday. 
</P>
<P>
More than 250,000 doses of anabolic steroids were confiscated from Woods' house 
in the 600 block of Shenandoah Street on Friday night in a raid by local, state 
and federal law enforcement agencies. Officials said it was the largest such 
seizure in the county and one of the largest in the state. 
</P>
<P>
Also seized at Woods' house was equipment suspected of being used in drug 
manufacturing, including a respirator, electronic scales and more than 800 
empty bottles as well as four automatic handguns and $30,000 in cash. PSYCHE 
PASCUAL 
</P>
</TEXT>
