<TEXT>
<P>
MUCH ADO: Grove Shakespeare Festival staffers are wearing trumpet label pins 
nowadays as subtle political comment. 
</P>
<P>
It all started when a former Garden Grove councilman who voted against funds 
for the troupe said Shakespeare isn't part of American culture. A major donor 
retorted that a trumpet should sound at each councilman's Shakespearean 
reference. . . . The council hasn't budged an inch ("The Taming of the Shrew"), 
but there is something in the wind ("The Comedy of Errors"). Tonight the 
festival will ask that its lease be relaxed and intends to fight till the last 
gasp ("King Henry the Sixth, Part I"). Lily Eng and Jan Herman 
</P>
