<HEADLINE>
<P>
3-MILE FALL GETS HER $50 FOR LUGGAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MOSCOW 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A woman passenger survived a fall of three miles from a Soviet airliner and 
then won $50 compensation for the loss of her luggage. 
</P>
<P>
Larisa Savitska plunged to Earth from an Aeroflot plane after it collided in 
midair with a military aircraft. 
</P>
<P>
The Komsomolskaya Pravda newspaper said she was the only survivor when the 
AN-24 airliner and a military transport collided near the Chinese border in 
1981. The incident had been kept secret. 
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said Savitska is still recovering from her injuries and must 
travel regularly to Moscow and Vladivostok for treatment. 
</P>
<P>
The article did not say how Savitska had escaped death. 
</P>
</TEXT>
