<P>
INDEPENDENCE HERO ENDS 15-YEAR EXILE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kader Siddiqi, a hero of Bangladesh's independence struggle, returned home from 
a 15-year exile to a tumultuous welcome and pledged to help restore democracy 
to the South Asia nation. Tens of thousands swarmed over Dhaka's airport to 
greet Siddiqi -- known as "the Tiger" for his guerrilla exploits in the 1971 
war against Pakistan -- upon his return from Calcutta. He had been sentenced in 
absentia to life in prison for killing an army major and several other soldiers 
in a 1975 revolt. 
