ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; 
</P>
<P>
CENTER OFFERS HELP TO MALL SHOPPERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shoppers interested in picking up a bus schedule, fingerprinting their child or 
getting information on a bicycle license can do so at one place. 
</P>
<P>
The city of Mission Viejo and the Orange County Sheriff's Department are 
sponsoring a community resource center at the Mission Viejo Mall. 
</P>
<P>
The center, which will be manned six days a week by volunteers from the city's 
Senior Community Activity Team, is open from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m., Monday through 
Saturday, and will be on ongoing project at the mall. 
</P>
<P>
Residents will be able to fingerprint their children for identification 
purposes and pick up an Orange County Transportation District bus schedule. 
</P>
