<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; 
</P>
<P>
NEGOTIATIONS BEGIN ON HOUSING PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has taken the first step toward the construction of a 
three-story senior citizen housing project. 
</P>
<P>
In a unanimous vote, council members last week approved a six-month negotiating 
agreement with Axiom Development &amp; Investments Inc. of Van Nuys for a 
proposed 195-unit building with an adjacent 70,000-square-foot medical office 
building. 
</P>
<P>
The project would be on six acres on the east side of Palm Street, between 
Aspenwood Lane and Garden Grove Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
The council's vote begins a negotiating process between the developer and the 
city toward a binding development agreement. 
</P>
<P>
The council also has named Mayor W.E. (Walt) Donovan chairman of the 
redevelopment agency, and named newly elected Councilman Mark Leyes vice 
chairman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
