<P>
GUNSHOT KILLS MAN IN ANAHEIM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 27-year-old man died today after being struck in the back by a single gunshot 
Sunday night while trying to flee an altercation in a downtown alley, Anaheim 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
Robert Rosado, whose address was unknown by authorities, was pronounced dead at 
5:17 a.m. today at UCI Medical Center in Orange. 
</P>
<P>
Police said witnesses reported seeing three men fighting about 7 p.m. Sunday in 
an alley in the 500 block of East Wilhelmina Street. The witnesses said one of 
the men, who was later identified by police as Rosado, attempted to run from 
the fight. As he did, one of the two suspects pulled a handgun and fired once, 
hitting Rosado in the back. 
</P>
<P>
The men then fled on foot. Police say they do not know what set off the 
altercation and have made no arrests in the case. 
</P>
</TEXT>
